Foil is a scheduling DSL for Scala which is agnostic to the underlying
datetime library implementation. It has built-in hooks for the common 
libraries:

 - JODA
 - JSR-310 (javax.time)
 - Java Date/Calendar
 - Saturn

Please see the Wiki for more details: http://wiki.github.com/oxbowlakes/foil/
Or contact us on the mailing list:  http://groups.google.com/group/foil-scala-scheduling